# ============================================
# reCAPTCHA v3 Implementation Details
# ============================================
# Version: v3 (invisible, score-based)
# Score Range: 0.0 (bot) to 1.0 (human)
# Threshold: 0.5 (recommended - configurable in functions)
# Actions: 'contact' for contact form, 'newsletter' for newsletter
# No user interaction required (invisible)

# ============================================
# Klaviyo Configuration (Required for Newsletter)
# ============================================
# Get your Private API Key from Klaviyo Dashboard
# Account > Settings > API Keys > Create Private API Key
KLAVIYO_PRIVATE_API_KEY=your-klaviyo-private-api-key

# ============================================
# How to Set in Netlify
# ============================================
# 1. Go to Netlify Dashboard: https://app.netlify.com
# 2. Select your site
# 3. Go to: Site settings > Environment variables
# 4. Click "Add a variable" for each of the above
# 5. Set the same values for both "Production" and "Deploy previews"
# 6. Redeploy your site after adding variables

# ============================================
# Important Notes
# ============================================
# - NEVER commit actual passwords or secret keys to git
# - Use different SMTP credentials for production vs preview deploys for security
# - Test email delivery after setting environment variables
# - Check function logs in Netlify UI if emails aren't sending
# - Graceful degradation: Forms work even if reCAPTCHA is not configured (with warning)
# - Rate limiting: 10 minutes between submissions from same email
# - Honeypot field: Automatically filters bot submissions
# - reCAPTCHA v3: Invisible protection with score-based verification (≥0.5 threshold)
